5: I'm forming my own pirate crew!
12:
Amelia... Please leave the jokes to
the clownfish...
17:
It's not a joke! I seriously thought this
through, I swear!
22:
Our world's got some seriously
suspicious stuff going on in it, right?
25:
And the Crimson Blades aren't really
around anymore to deal with it.
28:
Hm... It's true that Marina's absence
has most definitely left an impact
on your world...
32:
Yeah, we're just not the same
without her. *sigh* That's my Czarina
for you...
36:
On top of all that, there's a group of
jerk pirates trying to creep into the
northern seas!
39:
The government isn't doing diddly
squat though. Something's fishy for
sure!
44: You sure know a lot about this.
51:
Anyway, this got me thinking...
Someone needs to step up and fill
the Crimson Blades' shoes. And
since I've got feet now, who better to
step into those shoes than yours
truly!
54: The world needs a new hero!
57:
Do you truly believe you can fulfill
that role, Amelia?
59:
You've been captured by humans
and had to be saved by them as
well... Surely you cannot—
66:
I promise I'll be fine! I'll show you I'm
not the old Amelia anymore!
73:
Those blasted Crimson Blades...
Come out and show your ugly faces,
you cowardly sea dogs.
78:
Who knows? Maybe he took a few
too many cannonballs to the head.
81: Hey! I can hear you, dammit!
85:
Another attack from below?! Turn on
the radar, you scallywags!
88:
C-Cap'n! There's nothing there! No
enemy boats in sight!
92:
Then HOW are we gettin' shot at?!
Look harder, dammit!
95:
B-but all I see are some really big
fish...
103:
Hehe, don't worry, we just hit you
with some sonic weaponry. Your
ship's totally undamaged!
110:
Y-you! Aren't you...? No, there's no
way! Who are you?!
115:
Wow, rude much? I can't believe you
forgot all about the mermaid you
locked in that teeny tiny tank...
118:
Well, sounds like you need another
introduction!
121:
The name's Amelia! And I'm the
captain of the Mermaid Pirates!
130:
The northern seas are MY turf now!
You mess around here, and you'll be
swimming with the fishies! And not
the nice ones either!
135:
Wh-what makes you think I'll listen
to some little gir—
139:
No one says you HAVE to listen to
us...
142:
But if you do, I wouldn't mind taking
you under my wing someday. If you
behave, that is.
161:
The hell are you dogs drooling
over?! Compared to the Crimson
Blades' captain, that little brat's—
170:
I get it... You assembled a crew of
mermaids who can move freely
underwater without a ship. Now
that's a nasty trick... I love it!
173:
I'm quite pleased to see that the
state-of-the-art weapons I
provided are performing well in the
field.
178:
Heh... It seems our little mermaids
are enjoying them. What do you
think, Colonel Selene?
183:
An excellent display of power. I'd like
to have them for my own unit, quite
honestly.
187:
She wasn't kidding. Those are some
strong connections.
191:
Well, that settles it, old man. She
ain't the same guppy that got
caught by humans anymore.
194:
My sweet little Amelia... She's grown
up before my very eyes...
201:
Looks like someone's got her head in
the clouds.
204:
The sky in Starview is great, but
we've got a pretty killer view out
here in the ocean, don't we? It's
because we're far from the city
lights.
208:
That's actually how I got caught that
time. I wanted to get a better view of
the sky, so I went up to the surface.
216:
After I was caught, I tried convincing
my captors to let me go, saying that
I didn't taste very good, but they just
didn't understand...
219:
But I'm the one who didn't
understand. I knew I was in danger,
sure, but I don't think I realized how
scary the situation was.
224:
Just when I was about to be
completely lost to that fear and
confusion...
229:
Czarina and the rest of you all came
to my rescue. With a few slashes,
bam! I was free! And it was so cool! I
fell in love with you all at first sight.
236: Now it's my turn to return the favor.
240:
Come on, Stellie, I'll show you
something super cool!
250: This is the world through my eyes.
254:
You know, Stellie, I'll never forget the
day I was saved. You were the first
one to try and break me out, right?
257:
You just grabbed a barrel and
charged at me, remember? No way
would I forget that!
260:
But you know, that just showed me
that this crew can do anything we
put our minds to!
263:
Be it land, sea, or even the sky!
Wherever you wanna go, I'll make
sure we get there!
